@startuml architecturalknowledgedb-website-projection-sequence
title ArchitecturalKnowledgeDB - Website And Atlas Projection Sequence

actor Maintainer
participant "AKDB SAD\n+ product-facts.yml" as Facts
participant "Website facts_loader\n+ product catalog" as Catalog
participant "Tool page\n+ deep dive content" as DeepDive
participant "Atlas data join" as Atlas
participant "Static build / deploy snapshot" as Build
actor "Website reader" as Reader

Maintainer -> Facts : update AKDB boundary, usage, integrations
Facts -> Catalog : fact overlay supplies category/status/summary/detail
Catalog -> Build : literal Outer Tool entry + snapshot fallback
Maintainer -> DeepDive : curate usage, working modes, benefits, integrations
DeepDive -> Build : render AKDB feature page
Facts -> Atlas : product identity + category join
Atlas -> Build : emit AKDB node and relationships
Build -> Reader : Outer Tools list, AKDB page, Atlas node

note over Facts,Build
  Website content can feature AKDB strongly,
  but source files and SAD/UML remain authoritative.
  The deploy snapshot exists because Cloudflare may not see the sibling Git repo.
end note

@enduml
